The letters with which Gregorius thus furnished Au- gustinus, which were transcribed at Rome by Nothelm for Beda, are all to be found among his Epistles, and Smith has collected them in his Appendix, No. vi. From these we may conjecture something of the route taken by Augustinus. Gregorius gives him letters to the bishops of MarseiUe, Aix, Arles, Vienne, and Autun; all within the kingdom of Burgundy.
